A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 17-7-70.1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to trial
2 upon accusations in certain felony and misdemeanor cases and trial upon plea of guilty or
3 nolo contendere, so as to allow for offenses that are not serious violent felonies, sexual
4 felonies, or other certain offenses to be charged by accusation of the district attorney; to
5 provide for definitions; to provide for conditions; to provide for related matters; to repeal
6 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Code Section 17-7-70.1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to trial upon
10 accusations in certain felony and misdemeanor cases and trial upon plea of guilty or nolo
11 contendere, is amended by revising subsection (a) and adding a new subsection to read as
12 follows:
13 "(a) As used in this subsection, the term:
14 (1) 'Serious violent felony' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code
15 Section 17-10-6.1.
16 (2) 'Sexual felony' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section 16-5-21.
